# Spring Boot API Coding Conventions

## Package Structure & Naming

- Follow `mil.tron.commonapi.<layer>` package hierarchy
- Organize layers: `controller`, `service`, `repository`, `entity`, `dto`, `exception`
- Group related features in subpackages (e.g., `controller/documentspace`, `service/pubsub`)
- Name entities with singular nouns (Person, Organization, not Persons)
- Name DTOs with `Dto` suffix (PersonDto, OrganizationDto)
- Name service implementations with `Impl` suffix (PersonServiceImpl)
- Name repositories with `Repository` suffix (PersonRepository)

## Controller Layer (@RestController)

- Use constructor injection exclusively
- No field injection (@Autowired on fields)
- No business logic in controllers
- Controllers only orchestrate: validate input, call service, return response
- Annotate ALL public methods with @Operation and @ApiResponses
- Include @Parameter annotations on all method parameters
- Document expected responses: 200, 201, 203, 400, 404, 409 as appropriate
- Use @PreAuthorize* custom annotations for authorization
- Specify media types explicitly: consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE
- Map API paths with ${api-prefix.v1} and ${api-prefix.v2} properties
- Return ResponseEntity<T> with explicit HttpStatus
- Use Pageable with @ParameterObject for paginated endpoints
- Use @Valid on @RequestBody parameters
- V2 endpoints should use @WrappedEnvelopeResponse for collection responses

## Service Layer (@Service)

- Define interface and implementation (e.g., PersonService, PersonServiceImpl)
- Use constructor injection exclusively
- No field injection (@Autowired on fields)
- All business logic lives in services
- Services operate on DTOs externally, entities internally
- Use @Transactional on methods that modify data
- Convert entities to DTOs before returning to controller
- Throw specific exceptions (RecordNotFoundException, BadRequestException, etc.)
- Never swallow exceptions
- Use DtoMapper or ModelMapper for entity-DTO conversion
- Use @Lazy on circular dependencies (e.g., OrganizationService ↔ PersonService)

## Repository Layer

- Extend JpaRepository<Entity, UUID> or CrudRepository<Entity, UUID>
- Add JpaSpecificationExecutor<Entity> for filtering/specification support
- Use Optional<T> return types for find methods
- Name query methods following Spring Data conventions (findBy*, existsBy*)
- Annotate with @Repository
- Define custom repository interfaces as <Entity>RepositoryCustom if needed
- Use @Transactional on delete operations
- Use @Query for complex queries with specific projections

## Entity Layer (@Entity)

- Use Lombok annotations: @AllArgsConstructor, @NoArgsConstructor, @Builder, @Getter, @Setter
- Use UUID as primary key type
- Use @Builder.Default for collections and UUIDs: `@Builder.Default private UUID id = UUID.randomUUID()`
- Use @CreationTimestamp and @UpdateTimestamp for audit fields
- Use @ManyToOne, @OneToMany, @ManyToMany with explicit @JoinColumn or @JoinTable
- Mark PII fields with @PiiField annotation
- Mark protected fields with @ProtectedField annotation
- Implement equals() and hashCode() based on id
- Add @PrePersist and @PreUpdate methods for sanitization if needed
- Use @JsonIgnore for constants and helper methods
- Use @Table(uniqueConstraints = ...) for composite uniqueness

## DTO Layer

- Use Lombok annotations: @AllArgsConstructor, @NoArgsConstructor, @Builder, @Getter, @Setter, @EqualsAndHashCode
- Use javax.validation annotations: @Valid, @Email, @Size, @NotNull
- Use custom validation annotations from mil.tron.commonapi.validations
- Mark PII fields with @PiiField annotation
- Mark readonly fields with @Schema(accessMode = Schema.AccessMode.READ_ONLY)
- Mark non-patchable fields with @NonPatchableField
- Use @JsonInclude(JsonInclude.Include.NON_NULL) on optional fields
- Use @Schema annotations for OpenAPI documentation
- Use @Builder.Default for collections and UUIDs
- Keep DTOs in mil.tron.commonapi.dto package

## Exception Handling

- Throw specific exceptions: RecordNotFoundException, BadRequestException, ResourceAlreadyExistsException
- All custom exceptions in mil.tron.commonapi.exception package
- Use @ControllerAdvice for global exception handling
- ExceptionResponse shape: timestamp, status, error, reason, path, errors (optional)
- Never catch and swallow exceptions
- Log exceptions in @ControllerAdvice handlers, not in services
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes with exception responses
- Use IllegalModificationBaseException for EFA (Entity Field Authority) violations

## Validation

- Use javax.validation annotations on DTOs: @Valid, @Email, @Size, @NotNull
- Custom validators in mil.tron.commonapi.validations package
- Use @ValidDodId for DOD ID validation
- Use @ValidPhoneNumber for phone validation
- Use @NullOrNotBlankValidation for optional strings
- Apply @Valid to @RequestBody parameters in controllers
- Services should assume DTOs are pre-validated by controller layer
- Throw BadRequestException for business validation failures

## Logging

- Use Apache Commons Logging: `private final Log logger = LogFactory.getLog(CommonApiLogger.class)`
- Do NOT use @Slf4j or java.util.logging
- Log at WARN level for: exceptions, data integrity issues, security events
- Log at INFO level for: significant business operations (optional)
- Do NOT log at DEBUG level in production code
- Log structured messages: include entity IDs, operation type, relevant context
- Redact PII in log messages
- Log in @ControllerAdvice exception handlers, not in services
- Include sanitized request/response bodies for trace logging

## OpenAPI Documentation

- Annotate all @RestController classes
- Add @Operation(summary = "...", description = "...") on every public method
- Add @ApiResponses with all expected response codes
- Add @ApiResponse for each status: 200, 201, 203, 400, 404, 409
- Include content = @Content(schema = @Schema(implementation = Dto.class))
- Use @Parameter on all method parameters with description
- Use @Schema on DTO fields for documentation
- Use ExceptionResponse.class for error response schemas
- Document pagination headers with @Header annotation

## Testing

- Place tests in src/test/java mirroring src/main/java structure
- Name tests: <ClassName>Test.java
- Use @ExtendWith(SpringExtension.class) with @SpringBootTest
- Use @TestPropertySource(locations = "classpath:application-test.properties")
- Use @AutoConfigureMockMvc for controller tests
- Use @MockBean for service dependencies
- Use @WithMockUser for authentication tests
- Use JUnit 5: @Test, @BeforeEach, @Nested
- Use AssertJ for assertions: assertThat()
- Use Mockito for mocking: when(), verify(), ArgumentCaptor
- Test controllers via MockMvc: perform(), andExpect()
- Aim for unit tests on services, integration tests on controllers

## Security

- Use custom @PreAuthorize* annotations defined in mil.tron.commonapi.annotation.security
- Examples: @PreAuthorizePersonRead, @PreAuthorizePersonCreate, @PreAuthorizePersonEdit, @PreAuthorizePersonDelete
- Use @PreAuthorizeOnlySSO for SSO-only endpoints
- Apply security annotations at controller method level
- Extract authenticated user via Authentication parameter (optional)
- Do NOT implement authorization logic in services
- Use @PiiField to mark sensitive data
- Use @ProtectedField for EFA-controlled fields

## What NOT to Do

- NO field injection: never use @Autowired on fields
- NO business logic in controllers
- NO swallowed exceptions: never catch without rethrowing or logging
- NO direct entity exposure: always convert to DTO
- NO hardcoded values: use application.properties with @Value or ApplicationProperties
- NO @Slf4j or other logging frameworks: use Apache Commons Log
- NO returning List<Entity> from controllers: use DTOs
- NO missing OpenAPI annotations on public endpoints
- NO validation logic in services: validate in DTOs
- NO raw SQL in repositories: use @Query with JPQL or query methods
- NO DELETE without @Transactional
- NO Optional as method parameter type
- NO exposing internal error details to clients: use generic messages for 500 errors
- NO deprecated endpoints without @Deprecated and documentation

## Optional Conventions

- (Optional) Use @CacheConfig and caching annotations on services
- (Optional) Use @Transactional(readOnly = true) for read operations
- (Optional) Use Specification pattern for complex filtering
- (Optional) Use @JsonIgnore on utility methods in entities
- (Optional) Use @Builder.Default for default values
- (Optional) Add JavaDoc comments on complex service methods
